The paper analyzes the social network properties of the ERC20 protocol compliant crypto-coins' trading data, which involves the study of social signals and network dynamics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper also deals with blockchain technology and network theory.
